  "read": {
    "memory_vs_compute_bound": "The original MBS4 no-AC failure was memory-capacity/transient-materialization bound, but the surviving late-step MORI/MoE performance wall is padded-GEMM compute inflated by route imbalance. Step 4 has the same order of true assignments as the uniform owner probe, but padding multiplier rises from 1.05x to about 22x mean and 44x max.",
    "why_gemm_bucket_explodes": "The current padded local VJP forms tensors shaped [local_experts, max_count, hidden/intermediate]. When one or a few local experts receive tens of thousands of routes, every local expert is padded to that max_count, so W13/W2/Wgrad/Dgrad GEMMs perform huge amounts of zero-padding work and allocate huge padded slabs.",
    "what_this_means_for_mori": "MORI dispatch/combine is not the first bottleneck. combine_dx is mostly the peer-arrival wait/return partner of imbalanced owner VJP. The next speed path should remove max-count padding for imbalanced routes, not just increase VRAM or tune MORI collectives.",
    "next_candidate": "Add an opt-in compact/expert-loop owner VJP for high-padding cases, then benchmark e2e TFLOPs and memory against the retained padded MBS4 run."
